y with my answers. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><strong><span style="font-size:11.0pt">Round 3 (F2F Interview): </span></strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><span style="font-size:11.0pt">This round was a mix of technical and HR questions. This round started with a brief introduction. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><span style="font-size:11.0pt">The questions were simple and basic such as swapping of two numbers without using temporary variable. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><span style="font-size:11.0pt">Some basic questions related to DBMS and OS were asked. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><span style="font-size:11.0pt">1. Difference between semaphore and mutex. Give an example where mutex can be used. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><span style="font-size:11.0pt">2. Indexing in DBMS. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><span style="font-size:11.0pt">3. Difference between inner join and outer join. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><span style="font-size:11.0pt">He then asked me why I wanted to join Walmart Labs. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><span style="font-size:11.0pt">After the technical interviews, I was called for the HR round. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><strong><span style="font-size:11.0pt">Round 4 (HR Round): </span></strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><span style="font-size:11.0pt">This round started with a brief introduction. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><span style="font-size:11.0pt">He asked about my projects that I had done in a team. He asked me the difficulties I faced while working in a team. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Then some basic HR questions followed.</span></span></p>\r\n'),
(33, 'Walmart Labs by Abhinav Singh', '09-28-17', 'akki', 'walmartlabs-logo.jpg', 'Walmart,Walmart Labs,interview,experience,internship', '<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:center"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><strong><span style="font-size:16.0pt">@WalmartLabs</span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:center"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><strong><span style="font-size:16.0pt">Abhinav Singh</span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><strong><u>Round 1 (Coding Round) : </u></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">3 coding questions.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">1. n cities connected as a ring. Find number of ways to reach destination from source with exactly k moves. (30 Points)</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">2. n rows, each row has different number of seats, cost of a seat is number of seats left in that row. Find maximum profit that can be gained. (30 Points)</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">3. n vacation days given.&nbsp;&nbsp; 4 possibilities&nbsp; :&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 0 &ndash; yoga camp is closed, coding contest is off,&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 1 &ndash; yoga camp is open, coding contest is off,&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 2 &ndash; yoga camp is closed, coding contest is on,&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 4 &ndash; both open. Now on a day, we can either do yoga (if yoga camp is open), or we can give coding contest (if contest is open) , or we can REST. If on a day yoga was done, we cannot do yoga on the next day. Find minimum possible number of REST days (Dynamic Programming).&nbsp; (40 Ponts)</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><strong><u>Round 2 (Technical Interview) :</u></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">1. <a href="http://www.geeksforgeeks.org/stock-buy-sell/" style="color:#0563c1; text-decoration:underline">http://www.geeksforgeeks.org/stock-buy-sell/</a></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">2. It was a pretty complex and long question of linked list which later turned out to be a binary tree. Can&rsquo;t explain and couldn&rsquo;t find it online anywhere. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><strong><u>Round 3 (Technical Interview) :</u></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">1. Find LCA in n-ary tree.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">2. Some theoretical questions of Operating System (related to &ldquo;cores&rdquo;, such as dual core and multi-core. I simply said &ldquo;I don&rsquo;t know&rdquo; to some complex questions).</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">3. LRU cache implementation theory and code.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">4. PUZZLE : <a href="http://www.mathsisfun.com/puzzles/weighing-10-bags-solution.html" style="color:#0563c1; text-decoration:underline">http://www.mathsisfun.com/puzzles/weighing-10-bags-solution.html</a></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><strong><u>Round 4 (Partially Technical :P) :</u></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">1. Swap 2 numbers without using temporary variable.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">2. Some questions regarding stacks and queues.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">3. Definition, difference, uses and implementation of Semaphores and Mutex.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">4. Some theoretical concepts of Operating System such as Virtual Memory and others topics.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">5. Some easy questions related to palindrome.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">6. A string is given. Find the number and frequency of repeating substring in that string.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Then he asked me some non-technical questions such as what kind of job I want, what are my best attributes and few other questions.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><strong><u>Round 5 (HR Round) :</u></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Although interview went for 20-25 minutes and it was a proper formal HR interview round, NO one was eliminated from this round. Normal HR questions were asked.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><strong><u>Result :</u></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">As it can be figured out from what I have written for Round 5&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Selected&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in">&nbsp;</p>\r\n'),
(34, 'Walmart Labs by Sonu Kumar Sharma', '09-28-17', 'akki', 'walmartlabs-logo.jpg', 'Walmart,Walmart Labs,interview,experience,internship', '<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><strong><span style="font-size:15.0pt">Walmart Labs&nbsp; 1st Round Online Coding Questions:</span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:15.0pt">1. At a time a man is given choices to either play or to read alternatively. i.e. if in ith day he was reading then he cannot read on (i+1)th day. But not both simultaneously .</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:15.0pt">You are given an array of the possible activities of each day in form of 0,1,2,3. 0 represents he cannot do anything, 1 represents he can read only, 2 represents he can play only and 3 represents he can read and play both. So, you have to find the maximum no of activities he can do for n days.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:15.0pt">Input:-&nbsp; 2 2 2 2</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:15.0pt">Output: 2</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:15.0pt">Explanation:-&nbsp;&nbsp; Possible cases: 1) 2 0 2 0</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:15.0pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 2) 0 2 0 2</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:15.0pt">2. You are given an array of n&nbsp; int numbers between 0 to 10^5. Now, you have take m&nbsp; numbers from the array and keep adding the value of the elements before decreasing it by 1 &nbsp;to the answer&nbsp; such that such that their sum is maximum. &nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:15.0pt">1&lt;=m&lt;= sum of array elements i.e. A[1]+A[2]+---+A[n]</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:15.0pt">1&lt;n&lt;10^5</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:15.0pt">Input : n=5 8 7 6 5 4 and m=7</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:15.0pt">Ouput: &nbsp;45</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:15.0pt">Explanation : 8 + 7 + 6 + 7 +6 +6&nbsp; +5&nbsp;&nbsp; =45 (max sum)</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:15.0pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Will be added soon.</span></span></span></p>\r\n');
