(45, 'Samsung by Nakul Deep Matta', '09-28-17', 'akki', 'samsung.jpeg', 'samsung,interview,experience,internship', '<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black">&nbsp;<strong><span style="font-size:11.0pt">Name</span></strong><span style="font-size:11.0pt">: Nakul Deep Matta </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><strong><span style="font-size:11.0pt">Company</span></strong><span style="font-size:11.0pt">: Samsung-Delhi R&amp;D </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><strong><span style="font-size:11.0pt">Cut-off</span></strong><span style="font-size:11.0pt">: 7.5 for CSE and 8.5 for ECE &amp; IT </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><strong><span style="font-size:11.0pt">Location</span></strong><span style="font-size:11.0pt">: Noida </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><strong><span style="font-size:11.0pt">CTC</span></strong><span style="font-size:11.0pt">: 14 LPA </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><strong><span style="font-size:11.0pt">Profile</span></strong><span style="font-size:11.0pt">: Engineer </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><strong><span style="font-size:11.0pt">Coding Round (No. of questions: 1, Duration: 3 hours): </span></strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><span style="font-size:11.0pt">The company first visited our campus on 10</span><span style="font-size:7.0pt">th </span><span style="font-size:11.0pt">Aug. But as no one able to crack the coding round, the company went without conducting any interview rounds. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><strong><span style="font-size:11.0pt">On-campus coding question (50 test cases): </span></strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><span style="font-size:11.0pt">Given n army camps, their size in size[], and their cost in cost[] </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><span style="font-size:11.0pt">You start from the 1st camp </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><span style="font-size:11.0pt">You can either pay the cost[i] for ith camp and proceed forward, </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><span style="font-size:11.0pt">or you can either buy the army of size[i] for 2*cost[i] </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><span style="font-size:11.0pt">or if you have enough soldiers to beat the army of size[i], you can battle without spending anything (but your soldiers will die) </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><span style="font-size:11.0pt">You have to find the minimum cost to travel all the posts, starting from 1. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><span style="font-size:11.0pt">Condition: Each army can battle only thrice or until it is dead from the battle, e.g. an army was </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><span style="font-size:11.0pt">bought at 1st post and different army was bought at 4th post, the 1st post army can only take part in </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><span style="font-size:11.0pt">their 3 battles while 4th post army can take part in their 3 battles. Those 3 battles for both posts </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><span style="font-size:11.0pt">army may or may not occur together, e.g. the 1st post army battles 2nd and 3rd post&rsquo;s army alone and battle 5th post&rsquo;s army along with 4th post&rsquo;s army. At this stage, all the remaining members of 1st post&rsquo;s army will have to leave and only 4th post&rsquo;s members will remain. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><span style="font-size:11.0pt">Then after days of requests by TPRs, the company finally gave another chance on a condition that eligible students will have to travel on their own to Samsung-Delhi office. 10 of us, all from CSE went there. Around 30+ students from NIT Hamirpur also came (they had a similar situation on their campus like ours) </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><strong><span style="font-size:11.0pt">Coding question at Samsung Delhi Office (10 test cases): </span></strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><span style="font-size:11.0pt">Given an equation, </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><span style="font-size:11.0pt">Y = a*x + b*x*floor (log2 n) + cx^3 and a variable K </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><span style="font-size:11.0pt">1 &lt;= a, b &lt;= 100, 0&lt;=c&lt;=100, Y&lt;2^63 &ndash; 1, x&gt;=1 </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><span style="font-size:11.0pt">a, b and c are also given </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><span style="font-size:11.0pt">We have to find the value of x for which Y=K, but as values for Y and K are very large, simple linear search for the value x would only solve few test cases but binary search would work fine for all test cases. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><span style="font-size:11.0pt">Those who solved all the test cases were shortlisted for further rounds. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><span style="font-size:11.0pt">Total shortlisted: 4 </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><strong><span style="font-size:11.0pt">Interview Round 1 (Technical Interview, Duration: 25 minutes): </span></strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><span style="font-size:11.0pt"> Find the minimum element from the array </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><span style="font-size:11.0pt"> Find 2 minimum elements from the array in one traversal </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><span style="font-size:11.0pt"> A river crossing puzzle involving 3 animals and a man </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><span style="font-size:11.0pt"> A profit loss question: Given a selling price for 2 bikes, and 25% profit was made on 1 bike and 20% loss was made on another, find the final profit or loss </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><span style="font-size:11.0pt"> Asked me about my Android Project </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><span style="font-size:11.0pt"> Some questions about Android: What is an activity, what are Intents - their types etc. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><span style="font-size:11.0pt"> Some questions on DBMS: What is a foreign key, composite key etc. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><span style="font-size:11.0pt"> 1 question from CSS about responsive design </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><span style="font-size:11.0pt">Be ready for some rapid-fire questions about DBMS/JAVA/OS basics. For everyone, this round lasted for maximum 30 minutes. No one was rejected in this round. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><strong><span style="font-size:11.0pt">Interview Round 2 (HR Interview, Duration: 20 minutes): </span></strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><span style="font-size:11.0pt"> Tell me about yourself </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><span style="font-size:11.0pt"> Questions about family and background </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><span style="font-size:11.0pt"> Why Samsung </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><span style="font-size:11.0pt"> What values can you provide to Samsung </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><span style="font-size:11.0pt"> How long did you take to finish the code in first round </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><span style="font-size:11.0pt"> Why should I select you instead of someone else </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><span style="font-size:11.0pt"> What are your weaknesses </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><span style="font-size:11.0pt"> What do you like and hate about Samsung (as I had spent half a day at their office by that time) </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><span style="font-size:11.0pt">This round&rsquo;s duration varied from 10 minutes to 40 minutes. For some students from NIT Hamirpur, it was a stress interview, but no one was rejected here as well. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><strong><span style="font-size:11.0pt">Result: </span></strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><span style="font-size:11.0pt">All 4 of us got in!! (10 out of 30+ students from Hamirpur cleared the coding round and all of them were selected too) </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><strong><span style="font-size:11.0pt">Tips: </span></strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><span style="font-size:11.0pt"> Try to solve the coding question and cover all the test cases. Even if you fail to solve just 1 test case, you won&rsquo;t be shortlisted. One of us asked a different HR about our chances of selection, she said that it was 90% for those who clear the coding test </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"><span style="font-size:11.0pt"> If you belong to ECE background, you will have 2 technical interviews instead of 1 </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in">&nbsp;</p>\r\n');
INSERT INTO `cmsposts` (`post_id`, `post_title`, `post_date`, `post_author`, `post_image`, `post_keywords`, `post_content`) VALUES
(46, 'VISA by Raman Shukla', '09-28-17', 'akki', 'Visa.jpg', 'VISA,interview,experience,internship', '<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">&nbsp;<strong><span style="font-family:&quot;Microsoft JhengHei&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:black">Name </span></span></strong><span style="color:black">&ndash;</span><span style="font-family:&quot;Microsoft JhengHei&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"> Raman Shukla </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><strong><span style="font-family:&quot;Microsoft JhengHei&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:black">Branch </span></span></strong><span style="color:black">&ndash;</span><span style="font-family:&quot;Microsoft JhengHei&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"> CSE </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><strong><span style="font-family:&quot;Microsoft JhengHei&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:black">Stipend/CTC Offered </span></span></strong><span style="color:black">&ndash;</span><span style="font-family:&quot;Microsoft JhengHei&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"> 22 lpa </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><strong><span style="font-family:&quot;Microsoft JhengHei&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:black">Job Profile </span></span></strong><span style="color:black">&ndash;</span><span style="font-family:&quot;Microsoft JhengHei&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"> Software Engineer </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><strong><span style="font-family:&quot;Microsoft JhengHei&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:black">Location </span></span></strong><span style="color:black">&ndash;</span><span style="font-family:&quot;Microsoft JhengHei&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"> Bangalore </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:&quot;Microsoft JhengHei&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:black">The hiring process was as follows </span></span><span style="color:black">&ndash;</span> </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><strong><span style="font-family:&quot;Microsoft JhengHei&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:black">First Round (Online Coding Round) </span></span></strong><strong><span style="color:black">&ndash;</span></strong><strong><span style="font-family:&quot;Microsoft JhengHei&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"> 2 hours </span></span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:&quot;Microsoft JhengHei&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"> 4 coding questions on Recursion, BST, Number arithmetic and simple adhoc. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:&quot;Microsoft JhengHei&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"> 3 were easy and 4</span></span><span style="font-size:7.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Microsoft JhengHei&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:black">th </span></span></span><span style="font-family:&quot;Microsoft JhengHei&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:black">was a bit tricky but solvable. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:&quot;Microsoft JhengHei&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"> Top 40 from the coding round made to the face to face interviews. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><strong><span style="font-family:&quot;Microsoft JhengHei&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:black">Second Round (Face to face interviews) </span></span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><strong><span style="font-family:&quot;Microsoft JhengHei&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:black">First Interview (Technical) </span></span></strong><strong><span style="color:black">&ndash;</span></strong><strong><span style="font-family:&quot;Microsoft JhengHei&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"> 30 minutes </span></span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:&quot;Microsoft JhengHei&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"> Firstly, she asked me to tell about myself. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:&quot;Microsoft JhengHei&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"> My biggest achievement in studies after coming to college. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:&quot;Microsoft JhengHei&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"> Why did I choose Android development ( in response to my answer in the previous question) </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:&quot;Microsoft JhengHei&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"> Two technical questions </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:&quot;Courier New&quot;"><span style="color:black">o </span></span><span style="font-family:&quot;Microsoft JhengHei&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:black">We have a database in the form of a table which has some defined columns and numerous rows each having information about a person. The columns were the name, <strong>the department number </strong>to which he belongs, <strong>a unique ID, </strong>DOB, salary etc. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:&quot;Microsoft JhengHei&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:black">Then she asked me to suggest a data structure to store all the information such that given a department number, I need to output the information of all the people who belong to it. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:&quot;Microsoft JhengHei&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:black">(Hint </span></span><span style="font-family:&quot;Courier New&quot;"><span style="color:black">&ndash;</span></span><span style="font-family:&quot;Microsoft JhengHei&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"> Use Array of pointer to structure). </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:&quot;Courier New&quot;"><span style="color:black">o </span></span><span style="font-family:&quot;Microsoft JhengHei&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:black">Given a set of a large number of strings and a function that tells the lexicographical order between two given strings, suggest a data structure that sorts this set of strings with least complexity. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:&quot;Microsoft JhengHei&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:black">(Hint - Using Array of pointers). </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><strong><span style="font-family:&quot;Microsoft JhengHei&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:black">Second Interview (Technical) </span></span></strong><strong><span style="font-family:&quot;Courier New&quot;"><span style="color:black">&ndash;</span></span></strong><strong><span style="font-family:&quot;Microsoft JhengHei&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"> 1 hour </span></span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:&quot;Microsoft JhengHei&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"> The interviewer asked me to describe my college. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:&quot;Microsoft JhengHei&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"> My strengths and weaknesses. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:&quot;Microsoft JhengHei&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"> Any social work done by me in the college. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:&quot;Microsoft JhengHei&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"> What is a Data Structure? Types of data structures. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:&quot;Microsoft JhengHei&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"> Can a structure point to itself? </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:&quot;Microsoft JhengHei&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"> What is it called? (After a Yes) </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:&quot;Microsoft JhengHei&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"> Which is better, an array of pointers or a 2-D Array? </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:&quot;Microsoft JhengHei&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:black"> Difference between a Mutex and a Semaphore. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0