ight:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:ArialMT">I told him about the time when I started it all with a login panel and how It got attacked by SQL</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:ArialMT">Injection.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:ArialMT">He asked me the difference between Encoding,Encryption,Hashing</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:ArialMT">Types of Encryption?Symmetric, Asymmetric(quite trivial).</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:ArialMT">I explained both encryption to him by famous Alice Bob example and public Key Private Key</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:ArialMT">thing.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:ArialMT">Http stateless or </span>&mdash;&ndash;<span style="font-family:ArialMT">?</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:ArialMT">I replied with stateless.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:ArialMT">If stateless how it manages to provide user specific contents?</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:ArialMT">Cookie I said(he was happy)</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:ArialMT">Cross Side Scripting?</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:ArialMT">he asked me the language and IDE</span>&rsquo;<span style="font-family:ArialMT">s i used for Android Development ans iOS?</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:ArialMT">Asked me about various validations i put in a form..</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:ArialMT">Fours types of methods used in form?</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:ArialMT">I gave two names </span>&ldquo;<span style="font-family:ArialMT">GET</span>&rdquo;<span style="font-family:ArialMT"> and </span>&ldquo;<span style="font-family:ArialMT">POST</span>&rdquo;<span style="font-family:ArialMT">..i did not know the other two(PUT and DELETE)</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:ArialMT">I told me the explain difference between GET and POST</span><span style="font-family:ArialMT">Happy with answer</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:ArialMT">Why GET preferred over POST?</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:ArialMT">I told him that GET was vulnerable to data leaking as variable and value was present in the</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:ArialMT">URL.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:ArialMT">He was expecting the following answer.Due to limitation in size of URL we cannot use GET to</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:ArialMT">pass large number of values..which POST does easily</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:ArialMT">Why would I like to join VISA than greatly growing startup like Flipkart?[Stuck with VISA no</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:ArialMT">matter what they tell you]</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:ArialMT">No of threes in all numbers from 1n?.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:ArialMT">Better than O(n)</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:ArialMT">He finished the Interview with this puzzle..</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:ArialMT">How many times minute and hour hand would overlap in 24 hours..[Answer 22]</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><strong><span style="font-family:Arial-BoldMT">ROUND 3: HR Round(</span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><strong><span style="font-family:Arial-BoldMT">810</span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><strong><span style="font-family:Arial-BoldMT">minutes)</span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:ArialMT">He asked to tell something about myself and things I learnt in last three years?</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:ArialMT">I told him about myself ,my area of Interest,various projects I did,Technical Fest</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:ArialMT">[Avishkar,Techkriti] .I followed with personal skills like facing difficult situations..helping friends</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:ArialMT">(continuously spoke for 57</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:ArialMT">minutesin</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:ArialMT">flow)</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:ArialMT">Asked me if i had any questions for him?[Never Say NO to this question always</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:ArialMT">have something</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:ArialMT">to ask]</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:ArialMT">I asked him a couple of questions related to work and technologies in VISA.</span></span></span></p>\r\n'),
(48, 'Oracle by Rahul Singh', '09-28-17', 'akki', 'oracle-1.jpg', 'oracle,interview,experience,internship', '<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black">&nbsp;<span style="font-size:11.0pt">Oracle Profile: Server Tech Engineer Written Round: This round consisted of objective questions on Aptitude, Data Interpretation, Logical reasoning, C, OOPS, Algorithms, DS, Networking. Each section had specified time limit. Questions were of moderate difficulty. Coding Round: This Round was only for those who applied for Server Tech Engineer. No eliminations were made in this round. But this was the main criteria for clearing 1st Technical Round. There were two questions to be completed in an hour. 1. Print given string in vertical zigzag pattern. I/P: Number of row followed by the string. O/P: Vertical Zigzag pattern. Case #00: I/P: 3 COMPANYISHIRING O/P: CASIOPNIHRNMYIG 2. Make all possible combination of given string such that it consists of a vowel of the string and all the letters must be in ascending order. 1st Technical Round: The interviewer asked me about the approach which I used to in the coding round. He suggested me a different approach but I replied that his approach will take more space than mine. He asked number of questions 1. Difference between structure and union. Explain with example. 2. What is LRU? 3. Minimum Spanning Tree (Kruskal/Prim) 4. Complexity of sorting algorithms 5. Difference between Merge and heap sort 6. Complexity of my code ,,,,,,I don&#39;t remember rest He asked me being an electronics student what do you know about DBMS. I replied that I don&#39;t know much about it but convinced him that I can excel in this field. Then he asked me about my internship project during Thailand. I explained him. Since my project was based on Image processing he just asked the algorithms involved. Then he asked about all the projects mentioned in my resume. 9 students were shortlisted for 2nd round. 2nd Technical Round: Interviewer had a copy of my resume and remarks made by 1st interviewer. He closely examined my resume. Then he started with design based problem. &quot;Today we are in digital world. Design a restaurant such that no paper work (Right from the entrance to exit) is involved. Mention all the Data Structures needed in each step. I don&#39;t want any verbal explanation. Take as much sheet and time as you can.&quot; This was the deciding factor in this round. I tried my best to impress him. He asked me to find out a duplicate and missing number. He kept adding conditions to it. I kept optimizing the solutions of each problem until he was satisfied. Explain your first project. Are you thinking of commercializing it? Why do you want to switch to software? </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">7 student were shortlisted for HR round. HR round: HR round of Oracle is a formality but you never know what&#39;s gonna happen. After a while I went for HR round. She asked me to sit. 1. Introduce yourself. 2. Do you want to go for Masters? 3. Tell me about your ups and downs in life 4. Your strength since I was from Nepal she asked about the Nepal earthquake and how things are now. She asked my experience of Thailand. She told me that you have more number of project compared to the rest students. How do you manage time? She asked me about size of my T-shirt, location preference,,,,J While I was about to leave she told me not to worry since my result will be positive. This was the most beautiful moment of my life. Results were announced after 4-5 hours. And I had my name in the list J Keep working hard, control your emotions and be confident at the time of interview.</span></span></p>\r\n');
